37
00:02:56,680 --> 00:03:00,680
they are doing a full review that's supposed to be finished by October.

38
00:03:00,820 --> 00:03:05,820
So I know people think of a review as a bit of a yawner and won't produce anything for you,

39
00:03:05,880 --> 00:03:08,960
but this is a pretty critical stage for our climate plan.

40
00:03:09,320 --> 00:03:12,220
As you know, we haven't been meeting our targets.

41
00:03:12,220 --> 00:03:19,100
And we've unfortunately in a bit of a lull in terms of public enthusiasm for climate action.

42
00:03:19,100 --> 00:03:27,020
I'm hoping and I'm very confident that it's cyclical and we will resume our focus on climate

43
00:03:27,020 --> 00:03:29,540
when we get through some of these other challenges that we're facing.

44
00:03:29,540 --> 00:03:33,560
But we're not meeting our targets and we need to figure out how to do that.

45
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:41,960
So updating from the 2018 plan and the scope for these reviewers is everything's on the table.

46
00:03:42,140 --> 00:03:43,840
We're looking for a transformative change.

47
00:03:44,320 --> 00:03:47,600
We're looking for a paradigm shift in how we tackle climate.

48
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:50,540
And this industry will be a huge part of that.

49
00:03:50,620 --> 00:03:56,640
I'm not going to prejudge their results, but I know that electrification will be a major push.

50
00:03:56,760 --> 00:04:02,040
So we're really excited for the previous call to power and the one that's coming up.

51
00:04:02,160 --> 00:04:04,500
All of you are leading the way in this.

52
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:06,320
