77
00:05:57,420 --> 00:06:06,580
So to think that these bills will go from a draft 10 days ago to being law by the end of May,

78
00:06:06,640 --> 00:06:10,520
that is extremely quick, and we believe that they need the proper screening.

79
00:06:11,660 --> 00:06:17,600
So that's our job, to make sure that we don't sacrifice the rigor of environmental assessment

80
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:21,580
and the social license that we all know that we get from proper consultation.

81
00:06:21,580 --> 00:06:27,640
So I can't stress enough that the B.C. Greens obviously support development of renewable energy

82
00:06:27,640 --> 00:06:33,040
and are supportive of ways to speed this up so we can get these things built.

83
00:06:33,860 --> 00:06:39,980
But we are very wary of living too fast and seeing a social backlash.

84
00:06:40,240 --> 00:06:43,900
And we know that there is resistance to some of these, some communities.

85
00:06:44,020 --> 00:06:50,540
So you bring communities along, allow First Nations to participate, and those are key to success.

86
00:06:50,540 --> 00:06:57,060
We haven't heard that from some of the stakeholders so far, so we'll be examining the extent of this bill

87
00:06:57,060 --> 00:07:02,560
and these bills and trying to figure out how to make them work.

88
00:07:02,840 --> 00:07:06,180
So I don't, yeah, I'm not here to monologue.

